00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:41,080
So let's look at how to prioritize the right HR processes and AI use cases.

140
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:54,200
So our recommendation is to use the Gartner Use Case Assessment Framework, which evaluates each use case on two critical dimensions: value and feasibility.

141
00:12:54,200 --> 00:13:12,040
Now, value measures how much a particular use case could have, how much impact the use case could have on key HR value drivers like employee experience, workforce productivity, HR efficiency, all those things that you aligned with stakeholders on step one.

142
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:27,640
Feasibility looks at internal readiness, so data, people, process governance, and external factors like vendor maturity, proven customer success, and regulatory privacy or security considerations.

143
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:39,640
Now, using these two dimensions, HR AI use cases typically fall into three categories: likely wins, calculated risks, and marginal gains.

144
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:52,120
Now, this gives CHROs a disciplined way to decide which use case prioritization sessions, uh which use case prior which use cases matter.

145
00:13:52,120 --> 00:14:02,840
