Um, I hear concerns around um, you know, everybody has a chat has a chatbot, so and none of them speak with each other, which makes for terrible employee experience.

207
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:59,000
And there are also change management challenges where some segments of your workforce might just not want to speak with the board.

208
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,160
So it's an area where there's a lot of traps.

209
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:06,840
So you need to uh you need to you need to have a solid readiness plan associated with this.

210
00:21:06,840 --> 00:21:18,080
There are other areas here like voice of the employee, knowledge-based content generation, skills management, and labor market intelligence, uh, which are also emerging as uh likely wins here.

211
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:26,240
Uh, the labor market intelligence piece is uh is is is an interesting one.

212
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:27,440
It for sure is.

213
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:38,000
I think it's one of those situations where back in my days, and for those of who are listening to this and on the line with us right now, if you ever worked with compensation survey data, you go and appreciate this.

214
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:43,680
Every time we receive market survey data, we always looked at it and we kind of said, you know what, this is helpful.

215
00:21:43,680 --> 00:21:54,000
This is a year in the rear view, because by the time the data get into your hand, it's pretty much outdated just because of how long it took everyone to synthesize the type of survey data.

216
00:21:54,000 --> 00:22:12,000
So, because of the rise of labor market intelligence providers, what a lot of our audiences and a lot of clients I speak to are working on is how can I use AI enabled labor market intelligence to effectively give me another data point about what my competitors are doing.

217
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:13,120
What are they hiring for?

218
00:22:13,120 --> 00:22:14,880
Which geographies are they hiring for?

219
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:16,160
What skills are they hiring for?

220
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:17,920
How much are they paying for them?

221
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:24,240
And all of that data can now be accessed almost in near real time through labor market intelligence tools.

222
00:22:24,240 --> 00:22:29,360
And you don't have to wait for the market survey to come about.

223
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:50,560
You're essentially getting real-time or near real-time information in terms of your competitor movements, and that makes you that much better, even if it's like a fraction of a second, if you will, when it comes to getting the right talent, getting ahead of your talent plans and being able to business leaders in the right direction when it comes to the future of work and workforce planning.

224
00:22:50,560 --> 00:22:50,960
Right.

225
00:22:50,960 --> 00:22:54,960
No, it's a great input to uh strategic workforce planning.

226
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:59,360
Lots of CHROs um interested in learning more about this.

227
00:22:59,360 --> 00:23:09,400
Another area that several HR and IT leaders are excited about is the idea of a single AI powered front door for employees.

228
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:12,200
One entry point into the enterprise.

229
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:16,200
So you can see that we have highlighted that as a calculated risk here.

