00:54:51,880 --> 00:54:54,360
It's called the AI adoption triad.

540
00:54:54,360 --> 00:55:02,040
And it's a triangle that I keep whipping up time and time again because essentially, number one, we are currently in an era of ungovernable change.

541
00:55:02,040 --> 00:55:06,120
So take all of the awareness, desire, knowledge framework that you have known in the past.

542
00:55:06,120 --> 00:55:07,880
We don't work on that curve anymore.

543
00:55:07,880 --> 00:55:14,040
And we're just a little bit random right now, understandable and understandably so given the environment that we are currently in.

544
00:55:14,040 --> 00:55:17,560
Now, the AI adoption triad looks at three areas.

545
00:55:17,560 --> 00:55:23,160
Number one, from a change management perspective, did you give everyone the skills they need to be successful?

546
00:55:23,160 --> 00:55:28,840
So when you're asking everyone to play around and experiment, did you give them the basics that they needed to do that?

547
00:55:28,840 --> 00:55:31,480
Did you give them the tool set that they needed to do that?

548
00:55:31,480 --> 00:55:33,800
Then we look at motivation.

549
00:55:33,800 --> 00:55:35,960
How are you encouraging individuals?

550
00:55:35,960 --> 00:55:39,720
How are you giving them that level of psychological safety to thrive?

551
00:55:39,720 --> 00:55:43,560
How are you creating an environment that embraces failure in a way?

552
00:55:43,560 --> 00:55:47,640
Because experiments sometimes lead to failure, where people feel safe to fail.

553
00:55:47,640 --> 00:55:57,800
And with AI, especially with AI use cases, there is an expected level of failure in certain cases because you don't know if something that has work for someone else is going to work for your organization.

554
00:55:57,800 --> 00:55:59,560
So motivation is the second part.

555
00:55:59,560 --> 00:56:01,560
The third part is ease of use.

556
00:56:01,560 --> 00:56:15,280
So this is actually a very interesting technology design as part of change management question, because we're not just designing a system now in the name of designing a system, but we're designing a system accounting for all of the human psyche psychological factors.

557
00:56:14,840 --> 00:56:19,840
We're designing a system that accounts for how people will think and interact with the system.

558
00:56:20,000 --> 00:56:30,000
So being very intentional about where you place certain things, what systems and what frameworks you turn on, how you communicate about it, how you talk about it is also really important.

